<br>
Couple of old memories are hunting for a whole week in tox forest before giving up and taking the boat... I was fishing during the night because I couldn't see anything as an erudite and I was afraid I'd lose my corpse. I met a few people that saw me fishing and just sat beside me and pulled out a fishing rod and started chatting.<br>
<br>
My first groups in Western Karana, hunting bandits... staying there for hours and marvelling at how well the day/night cycle was done. I saw some pretty good roleplaying there. It took me I think 2-3 weeks playing pretty much 5-6 hours every day to get from level 10 to 16 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and I thought I was doing pretty good.<br>
<br>
Of course the classic run to Freeport from Qeynos. I waited until level 12 to do it, with bind affinity. I remember being amazed all the way with both bridges in NK, the ramp to highhold pass, with the fresques on the cliff. I made that trip to buy sharpening stones, because they weren't being sold in Qeynos.<br>
<br>
It's very hard to recreate the newbie feelings of discovery and amazement. The closest thing is when zones and expansions are released. It's just too easy to be melancholic and think that EQ was better in the &quot;old days&quot;.<br>
